Hey so what you've calculated there is the first part of what I've done; it chooses 10 unquie champions out of 124.
I went and multiplied is by a further 10 choose 2, for my answer. This 10 choose 2 divides the 10 champions into 2 teams .
To show the difference in an example;

GAME ONE: {{champion:266}} {{champion:103}} {{champion:84}} {{champion:12}} {{champion:32}} v.{{champion:34}} {{champion:1}} {{champion:22}} {{champion:268}} {{champion:432}}  
GAME TWO: {{champion:266}} {{champion:84}} {{champion:32}} {{champion:1}} {{champion:268}} v. {{champion:103}} {{champion:12}} {{champion:34}} {{champion:22}} {{champion:53}} 

In your method these two cases are treated equally as they have identical champs. 
In my method they have 2 different cases as it's two different teams.

Does that make sense?
